laboratory_examinations.findings: Lipase of 737, elevated outside normal range.
AST/ALT levels in the 200s, elevated outside normal range.

Multiple tiny layering gallstones in the gallbladder, choledocholithiasis with a 3mm stone in the distal common bile duct, and two haemorrhagic cysts in the kidneys measuring 4mm in the left and 6mm in the right kidney.
